<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 18 at 6:37PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A line of snow showers will affect Portage...Trumbull...central
Mahoning...eastern Medina...south central Cuyahoga...northern
Stark...Summit and northern Wayne Counties Until 730 PM EDT....
At 635 PM EDT, radar indicated snow showers along a line extending
from North Bloomfield to near Cuyahoga Falls to near Polk, moving
east at 30 mph. Webcams have shown initially wet roads becoming snow
covered and slick. As the sun sets pavement temperatures will
continue to cool which may lead to icy conditions.
HAZARDS INCLUDE...
Winds to 30 mph...
Visibility dropping to less than three quarters of a mile...
Snow and falling temperatures leading to snow-covered or icy roads...
Locations impacted include...
Akron, Youngstown, Warren, Medina, Ravenna, Cuyahoga Falls, Boardman,
Brunswick, North Royalton, Kent, Barberton, Green, Alliance, Hudson,
Wadsworth, Niles, Twinsburg, Tallmadge, North Canton and Streetsboro.
Use extra caution if you must travel. Rapid changes in visibility and
potentially slick roads may lead to accidents.</description>
